# C0 felt-intelligence dialogue: the first-impression session a new user has.
# This is NOT a pass/fail unit test (those live in tests/cases/*.chat). It is the
# conversation benchmark: expected lines are what a *satisfying* answer would
# contain (soft, substring match after normalization), and tests/chatbench.sh
# reports the fraction of turns that land. Most fail today on purpose -- the
# number is the honest baseline of felt intelligence, meant to climb as the
# C-series (TASKLIST) lands. Held-out: vary names/order in sibling .dlg files.
> hi
< hi there
> what is your name?
< parrot0
> who are you?
< parrot0
> what can you do?
< i can
> I have a dog named Rex
< rex
> what is my dog called?
< rex
> how are you?
< well
> thank you
< welcome
> bye
< goodbye
> what is 2 plus 2?
< 4
> what did we just talk about?
< dog
